{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the school was the obvious activities for a child, and as a result, you almost had this little pleasure that, hmm, I don't have to go to school every day, although you quickly realized that it wasn't the wishful thinking that came true.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was just the legal prohibition of Jews attending their regular schools.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The school itself was closed in, I believe, 1936.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And you were, from then on, sort of haphazardly attending classes that were clandestine, the teachers would hold in their homes, or perhaps in a larger facility.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We did still have some Jewish homes available of size large enough to attend, let's say, 10, 15 students, but the formal schooling had stopped, for me at least, in 1936.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "From 1936 to 1938, family life was totally disrupted because my father was forced to attend a-- not a concentration camp, but a forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was the vice-president of a chain of stores that-- that sold white goods, dresses, perfumes, soaps, and so on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was employed by a Jewish company, and-- which of course, was taken over by Nazi party members. and my father had not worked since 1936 with any regularity.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The business was not closed but prohibited to be owned by any Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in 1937, he was forced to-- he was forced into forced labor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The work he had to do was build the Maginot Line in France.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Germans on their side called it the Siegfried Line.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Siegfried Line was a fortification along the French border to prevent tanks from crossing borders either way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Obviously, my father being German, he had to build the Siegfried Line.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was the first, you know, major disruption of family life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I stayed home with my mother, who never worked.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
